    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.outdoorline.sk/en/">Outdoorline.sk</a> is a dedicated lightweight gear webshop from Slovakia. Located in the foot hills of the Tatras the owner Peter knows that going light in the mountains is a smart choice, and their OSS gear list reflects that.</p>

<p><img style="max-width:100%" src="https://farm8.staticflickr.com/7403/13469807744_450b027757_b.jpg#tl-506142292004831233;1043138249" class="alwaysThinglink" /><script async="" charset="utf-8" src="http://hikinginfinland.com//cdn.thinglink.me/jse/embed.js"></script></p>

<!-- more -->

<p>As a consumer I really think it is awesome that more and more dedicated lightweight webshops like <a href="http://www.outdoorline.sk/en/">Outdoorline.sk</a> open everywhere across Europe, making it for locals from near and far easy to buy top-notch gear. You can get some of the hard-to-get-in-Europe brands like Westcomb from Outdoorline.sk, and they also have a very good selection of great European brands like Röjk, Crux, Lightwave and Woolpower. But lets have a look what their OSS list looks like:</p>

